      <scopecontent id="aspace_375baec61d3e93dd0521f11a67ef21e3">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection comprises bookplates and other works by the artist Adri de Ruijter (sometimes spelled Adri de Ruyter), who was active in Holland in the mid-20th century. In addition to bookplates, the collection also contains greeting cards, engraved portraits, and monograms, including many examples of the artist's personal designs. Series V of this collection contains materials related to a bookplate and metal stamp commission by de Ruijter for Warren Hiram Lowenhaupt, former curator of the Yale Bookplate Collection.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_ecb50d324753f006aae6b75709a56e00">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into five series: I. Bookplates. II. Greeting Cards. III. Other Works. IV. Personal Designs. V. Warren Hiram Lowenhaupt Commissions.</p>  
      </arrangement>
